<section class="text-block">
    <h3 class="text-block_title">Solution</h3>
    <p class="text-block_copy">I started this design process by working with our Information Architect to define the most important functions of the shell. His reserach determined the placement of each feature in the responsive navigaiton. We moved the app switcher, user settings and bookmarks to the main mobile nav with a bento box button and kept the search and share funtionality in the top header for instant access.</p>

    <p class="text-block_copy">While designing the main mobile and tablet navigation, I was inspired by the Curtain navigation I had read about from <a href="https://medium.com/@supjoey/the-curtain-menu-redesigning-drop-down-navigation-for-mobile-bd63b555a3df#.kcki5bgyu" target="_blank">Playstation.com</a>. We needed to fit a lot of information into a small menu and the traditional accordian menu wasn't going to work. I wanted users to be able to scroll through a potential long list of applications while still be able to access other menu options. After some internal user testing around the office, this curtain model ended up being the perfect solution.</p>
</section>

